Weâ€™re aggressively growing Aera and seeking experienced Senior Recruiters to support this growth for our US teams. The recruiter we are seeking has experience sourcing and engaging mid to high level candidates. You'll partner closely with our leaders on their most critical hiring needs. These are highly visible, critical roles that offer extensive exposure to our leadership team. 
 
 Open to remote candidates in the US. 
 Responsibilities 
Own and manage the entire recruitment process, from preparing and posting job descriptions to sourcing candidates to managing the interview process to presenting offers and closing candidates 
Partner closely with our leadership team to define the requirements for open positions and prepare the job descriptions 
Build strong relationships with each of the hiring managers you support, such that you become a trusted advisor to them as they strategize how best to build their teams 
Manage the advertising of open roles and leverage relevant channels to attract inbound candidate interest. Explore innovative ways to build our employer brand, including by hosting meetups and on-site events 
Coordinate applications and responses, providing timely feedback both to the candidates and to your internal stakeholders 
Be a passionate advocate of Aera as a fantastic place to grow a career. Your enthusiasm for Aera is contagious! Articulate this value proposition to candidates in a way that engages and motivates them to join us on this adventure 
Deliver a compelling, thoughtful and memorable candidate experience to each person we interview 
Provide regular, data-driven updates to company leadership on recruiting progress 
 About You 
5-8+ years of experience as a Senior Recruiter, preferably at a technology company, where youâ€™ve seen effective, scalable recruiting processes in action 
Startup experience is highly desirable! 
Demonstrated experience engaging and closing passive talent for hard-to-fill roles 
Extensive knowledge of core recruiting processes (including interview scheduling, candidate debriefs, offer negotiations, etc.) 
Experience with Applicant Tracking Systems such as Lever is a must 
Experience running a structured interview process in a high volume recruiting environment 
Experience using a variety of traditional as well as innovative recruiting strategies such as leveraging social media to attract passive candidates 
A demonstrated commitment to taking a data-driven approach to managing the candidate pipeline and reporting on progress 
Organized with strong attention to detail, while also being innovative and flexible as the needs of the business evolve 
Energetic, with a positive and magnetic personality 
